data.enText: a person of French origin from Louisiana who speaks an old form of French, also called Cajun
data.chText: 卡津人（法裔路易斯安那州人，讲旧式法语）

data.enText: a type of music originally played by Cajuns , that is a mixture of blues and folk music
data.chText: 卡津音乐（一种法裔路易斯安那州人的音乐，布鲁斯歌曲混合民乐）

data.enText: connected with the Cajuns , their language, music or spicy cooking
data.chText: 卡津人（或语言、音乐、多香料烹饪）的

means: 卡津人(法裔路易斯安那州人，讲旧式法语)
卡津音乐(一种法裔路易斯安那州人的音乐，布鲁斯歌曲混合民乐)
卡津人(或语言、音乐、多香料烹饪)的

example.tran: 他们演奏了一些卡津音乐。

example.ex: ...a teacher from the Cajun area of Southern Louisiana...
example.tran: 来自路易斯安那南部的卡津人居住区的一位老师

value.def: Cajun means belonging or relating to a group of people who live mainly in Louisiana in the United States, and are descended from French people. Cajun is also used to refer to the language and culture of these people.
value.tran: 卡津人的;卡津语的;卡津文化的

value.def: A Cajun is a person of Cajun origin.
value.tran: 卡津人（居住在美国路易斯安那州的法国人后裔）

example.ex: ...the first book ever written in Cajun.
example.tran: 第一本用卡津方言写的书

value.def: Cajun is a dialect of French spoken by Cajun people.
value.tran: 卡津方言（一种法语方言）
